    <!-- content -->
    <div class="row">
      <!-- create VM instance -->
      <div class="col s7">
        <h4>Creating VM Instance</h4>
        <p class="indent">
          1. Create your instance name to: helloworld-vm <br>
          2. Boot disk: Google Debian GNU/Linux(default) <br>
          3. Machine type: changed to small(1 shared vCPU, 1.7 GB memory) <br>
          4. Check both HTTP & HTTPS boxes then create <br>
          5. Go into Networking > VPC Network > Firewall <br>
          6. Edit the rules for "default-allow-http" & "default-allow-https" adding port number 3000
        </p>
      </div>
      <!-- VM pictures -->
      <div class="col s5">
        <!-- add pictures later tongiht PLEASE -->
      </div>

      <!-- installation -->
      <h4>Install Node.js</h4>
      <p class="indent">
        1. Open up the shell by clicking SSH
        2. $ sudo apt-get update <br>
        3. $ sudo apt-get install -y nodejs <br>
        4. $ sudo apt-get install npm <br>
        5. Check if installations worked by using "node -v" & "npm -v"
      </p>

      <!-- starting project -->
      <h4>Install Express</h4>
      <p class="indent">
        1. Initialize a package.json file with the following command: $ sudo npm init <br>
        2. Add a start script to your package.json file: <br>
          "script":{ <br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;"start": "node server.js" <br>} <br>
        3. Install Express.js: $ sudo npm install --save express
      </p>

      <!-- creating project/server -->
      <h4>Code "Hello World!"</h4>
      <p class="indent">
        1. In the shell, create an server.js file with the following command: sudo vim server.js <br>
        2. Insert the following content: <br>
        const express = require('express'); <br>
        const app = express(); <br>
        app.get('/', (req, res) => { <br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;res.send('Hello World!'); <br>
        }); <br><br>
        app.listen(3000, function() { <br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;console.log("listening on port 3000"); <br>
          &nbsp;&nbsp;console.log("close the server with ctrl + c or ^ + c"); <br>
        });
      </p>

      <!-- Starting the server -->
      <h4>Start Node server</h4>
      <p class="indent">
        1. Start the server with the command: $ node server.js <br>
        2. Connect to it by clicking the VM's IP address and appending port 3000
        3. TA DA!
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
